=== EXECUTION ===

STEP 1 — discover stories
  Use Glob on '/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/user_stories/*.yaml'.
  Exclude _fixtures.yaml and _index.yaml.

STEP 2 — build RUN_DIR
  RUN_DIR='/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/status/story-runs/<ISO timestamp>'
  mkdir -p "$RUN_DIR"
  Use one timestamp for the whole run so screenshots group correctly.

STEP 3 — dispatch QA agents in parallel
  For each story, spawn one playwright-qa-agent via the Task tool.
  Issue them in the SAME message (parallel tool calls) — max 4 at a time.
  If there are more than 4 stories, batch: dispatch 4, wait for all,
  dispatch the next 4, etc.

  Prompt for each Task call — include ALL of the following:
    - story_name: <story.feature>
    - story_url: http://localhost:5173/ (or role-appropriate landing page)
    - workflow: a numbered list built from the story YAML.
      **PREFER `Assert` verbs over `Verify`** — Assert lines are checked
      by shell exit code (deterministic), Verify lines are LLM-judged
      (soft, PASS can be inflated). Apply these rewrites first:
        UI / DOM rewrites:
        - "user sees X" / "X is displayed" / "X appears"  → `Assert text "X" visible`
        - "user does not see X" / "X is hidden"           → `Assert text "X" not visible`
        - "button Y is disabled"                          → `Assert button "Y" disabled`
        - "button Y is enabled"                           → `Assert button "Y" enabled`
        - "field Z is empty / required"                   → `Assert textbox "Z" has value ""`
        - "redirect to /x"                                → `Navigate to /x` then `Assert URL path is "/x"`
        - "list has between N and M items"                → `Assert count of listitem matching ".*" between N and M`
        - "no errors on page"                             → `Assert no console errors` and `Assert no ErrorBoundary`
        Network/API rewrites (Patch B — verifies the actual HTTP
        status, not just the page DOM. Emit AFTER the click/submit
        that fires the request):
        - "form submits successfully" / "saved" / "created" → `Assert request POST matching ".*" status 2xx` and `Assert no console errors`
        - "login successfully"                              → `Assert request POST matching "(login\|signin\|auth)" status 2xx` then `Assert URL path is "<post-login route>"`
        - "delete X"                                        → `Assert request DELETE matching ".*" status 2xx`
        - "update X" / "edit X"                             → `Assert request (PUT\|PATCH) matching ".*" status 2xx`
        - "submit invalid form" / "shows validation error"  → `Assert request POST matching ".*" status 4xx` (the API SHOULD reject; soft frontend-only validation passes if no request fires)
        - "API returns 5xx" / "server error"                → `Assert request .* matching "<api>" status 5xx`
        - "no failed requests during flow"                  → `Assert no failed requests` at end of workflow
      Build steps from the YAML:
        1. For each acceptance_criterion.description → one workflow step.
           Apply the rewrite table above. Only fall back to
           `Verify <description>` when no Assert form fits.
        2. For each boundary_case → one step
           ("Attempt <case>" then `Assert text "<expected error>" visible`
            if the case names an expected error message; else `Verify`).
        3. For each error_scenario → one step (same Assert-first rule).
    - RUN_DIR: <RUN_DIR>/<story-kebab>
    - FRONTEND_URL: http://localhost:5173
    - viewport: 'desktop' unless the story mentions mobile/tablet

  Use subagent_type='playwright-qa-agent' for every dispatch.
  Do NOT invent workflow steps beyond what the YAML lists.
  Do NOT hardcode credentials — instruct the agent to read
    _fixtures.yaml via Read and use the fixture matching story.role.

STEP 4 — collect results AND write report INCREMENTALLY (critical: never batch the final write)

  Each agent returns a block like:
    STATUS: PASS|FAIL|CRASH
    STORY: ...
    | Step | Action | Result | Screenshot |
    FAILURE_DETAILS: ...
    SUGGESTED_STORIES: ...

  Parse each. Classify:
    - overall_status: PASS / FAIL / CRASH (from the STATUS line)
    - failure: first failing step + FAILURE_DETAILS text
    - priority:
        CRASH                              → P0
        FAIL on acceptance_criterion       → P1
        FAIL on boundary_case or error_scenario → P2
    - screenshot_dir: RUN_DIR/<story-kebab>

  AFTER EACH BATCH OF 4 (or fewer on the last batch) completes —
  BEFORE dispatching the next batch — write the FULL CURRENT STATE
  of STORY_QA_REPORT_react.md using the format below, with:
    - `story_runner_complete: false` while there are stories left to dispatch
    - the per-story table containing every story processed so far
    - running totals reflecting what's been processed (treat unstarted stories as not-yet-included)

  WHY this matters: a watchdog SIGKILL at the wall-clock budget loses
  ALL work that hasn't been persisted. v25-resume #3 evidence: 3 of 3
  story-runner subprocesses watchdog'd before they wrote a single
  report (cost: $0.000), discarding all partial results. Incremental
  writes ensure that even on kill, STORY_QA_REPORT_react.md reflects the
  stories that DID complete — far better than nothing.

  AFTER THE FINAL BATCH completes, do one last write with
  `story_runner_complete: true`. The verification gate checks that
  marker — `false` partials count as a Failed node (correct), but
  the data is preserved for downstream use (aggregate-story-results,
  bug-fix-pass, manual review).

STEP 5 — final write (set complete: true)

